Zimbabwe’s mass by-elections are rapidly approaching and former Harare Mayor Herbert Gomba has been arrested on allegations of violating the Electoral Act. eNCA correspondent Pindai Dube has more on this story. Courtesy of #DStv403 HARARE - Zimbabwe’s mass by-elections are rapidly approaching. Former Harare mayor Herbert Gomba, the opposition Citizens Coalition for Change candidate for the capital’s Ward 27, has been arrested on allegations of violating the Electoral Act. READ: Zimbabwe By-Elections | Police block opposition rally His lawyers believe he’s being harassed. The former Harare mayor has applied for bail and a ruling is expected. * eNCA’s Zimbabwe correspondent Pindai Dube reports.